node.title: Russian Diplomat Found Dead Outside Embassy in Germany: Report
node.alt: A view of the Russian embassy in Berlin on August 12, 2021 in Potsdam, Germany. A diplomat from the mission was reportedly found dead on October 19, 2021.
node.description: "Der Spiegel" reported on Friday that a 35-year-old man had been found outside Moscow's mission in Berlin.
node.content:
["A Russian diplomat was found dead by Moscow's embassy in Berlin last month, according to a report published by German media on Friday.", "Der Spiegel reported that the body of a 35-year-old was found by law enforcement at around 7.20 a.m. on October 19.", "The man is believed to have fallen from an upper floor of the embassy complex located on Behrenstrasse in the Mitte district of the German capital.", "The man had been accredited as second embassy secretary in Berlin since the summer 2019, Der Spiegel said. The German security authorities said he was an undercover officer of the Russian secret service the FSB.", "In details also reported by Russian news agency RIA, the body has been transferred to Russia.", "The Russian embassy said there had been a \"tragic accident\" but offered no further comment for \"ethical reasons,\" Der Spiegel reported.", "This is a developing story.", "", "
A view of the Russian embassy in Berlin on August 12, 2021 in Potsdam, Germany. A diplomat from the mission was reportedly found dead on October 19, 2021.
